## Email & Messaging Notifications

All emails are fire-and-forget: wrapped in `.catch(console.error)`, never thrown, never block the user response.

**V1 — Email only.** All notifications are sent via email (Resend). No SMS, no WhatsApp in V1.

**V2 — WhatsApp.** Once V1 is stable, the plan is to add WhatsApp as a messaging channel. WhatsApp is the end goal for real-time notifications (not plain SMS). Twilio env vars in the codebase are legacy placeholders and should be ignored until V2 work begins.

| Trigger | Recipient | Channel | Content |
|---|---|---|---|
| Student completes enrollment form | Teacher (`NOTIFICATION_EMAIL`) | Email | Full registration details in HTML email |
| Student completes enrollment form | Student | Email | Confirmation with school rules (see below) |
| Teacher creates a student account | Student | Email | Welcome + setup link to set password |

**From address:** `Nihanvi School of Dance <onboarding@resend.dev>` (placeholder — swap for verified domain before launch)

### School Rules — Included in Enrollment Confirmation (Email & SMS)

The following rules must be included verbatim in the confirmation email and SMS sent to the student after they complete the enrollment form:

> **Class Fee Policy**
> 1. All class fees MUST be paid in full regardless of student absence.
> 2. Lessons missed due to absence will be taught in the subsequent class and/or a makeup class.
>
> **Monthly Payment**
> 1. Fee is due in advance at the beginning of every month (no later than the 5th).
> 2. No fee proration without prior discussion with the teacher.
> 3. Payment is sent via Zelle to the teacher's registered number.

The Zelle number is stored in an environment variable (`ZELLE_NUMBER`) so it can be updated without a code change. It is substituted into the rules text at send time.

