## Code Conventions

- Mobile-first Tailwind: base class = mobile, then `sm:` / `md:` / `lg:` for larger screens
- Minimum touch targets 44×44px, minimum body font size 16px
- Client components that need form state use `useFormState` + `useFormStatus` from `react-dom` (React 18)
- `SubmitButton` is always a separate child component (needed to access `useFormStatus` context)
- Amounts stored in **cents** (integer) in the database, displayed as dollars in the UI
- `levelGroup` is a free-text string (e.g. "Beginner", "Intermediate", "Advanced") — not an enum
